    Product description

    Control Multiple Devices with One Tap

    Simplify your smart life by managing your devices in sync with your needs

    • How to connect smart plug?

      1. Download the Smart Life App and register for an account.

      2. Power on the plug and ensure that the indicator is flashing.

      3. The Smart Life App will automatically detect the plug.

      4. Follow the on-screen prompts to complete the connection process.

    • What to do when connection fails

      1. Unplug & hold 5s to reset.

      2. Reconnect via AP mode (watch the video guide).

      3. If not connecting, check for "SmartLife-xx" hotspot in AP-Mode. If not found, please reach out to the support team for a new one. If found, check your router settings.

    • How do I use the plug to work with third-party voice assistants?

      Connect the plug to the Smart Life App. Then, link your third-party service account (Alexa, Google Home, SmartThings) on the App. Alternatively, activate the "Smart Life" skill in the third-party voice assistant's App.

    • What should I do if my smart hom plug is broken?

      No need to worry! We've got you covered with a 2-year replacement service. If you encounter any problems, just reach out to us through Amazon or our official email, and we'll be more than happy to help!

      I should have purchased these years ago!     • Franz Gutentag
      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Works good, wish I had got them sooner.
      Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2025
      As many of the other reviews noted, these are easy to set up once you are aware of a few things which are noted below. I purchased both the small round indoor outlets and the larger outdoor outlets, so these hints apply to both items. The steps outlined in the... See more
      As many of the other reviews noted, these are easy to set up once you are aware of a few things which are noted below. I purchased both the small round indoor outlets and the larger outdoor outlets, so these hints apply to both items. The steps outlined in the instructions are actually pretty good but awareness of these hints will make it go much faster for you. 1- I configured my devices one at a time at the same outlet using the Smart Life app on my phone via the BLE mode. The first device is the most time consuming as you need to create a Smart Life account, identify your WIFI and put in your WIFI password. Once that is done, you don't need to do it again for subsequent devices, so it goes pretty fast after that. 2- As noted in the instructions, just plugging the device into an outlet will put the device into its pairing mode and it will appear in the app as "Smart plug x" where x = the number of devices added to the app. I did have one device that didn't appear after plugging it in, so pressing and holding the button on the device for 5 seconds put it into the pairing mode and it connected successfully. 3- As each device is detected, you should edit the name of the device from "Smart plug x" to a meaningful description e.g "Smart plug kitchen". I also wrote the description on the device with a sharpie as several of the devices will be used with Christmas lights and will be stored away in the off season. 4- I just wanted mine to power on and off as specific times. To do this, tap on "timer" for the device in the app and then tap on "add schedule". The thing to remember is that each schedule added only does one function (on or off), so if you want it to power on at a specific time, that's one schedule and if you want it to power off at a specific time, that's another schedule. The schedules just pile up in the order that you add them for the device and execute based on the time and the function (on or off) that you choose. Note that the indoor and outdoor devices behave a little differently from each other in the app because the outdoor devices have 2 individually configurable outlets, so it is a little more complicated but pretty obvious. You can also manually power the devices on and off via the app even with schedules in place.
